resource.name: Eswatini Encounter Profile
resource.description:
The Eswatini Encounter Profile inherits from .... This profile sets minimum expectations for the Encounter resource to record basic encounter
information for a patient. It specifies which core elements shall be present and constrains how the elements are used.

resource.name: Eswatini Procedure Profile
resource.description:
This resource is designed to record details of current and historical procedures performed on a patient.
This may include the start and stop dates of treatment like IPT.

resource.description: This resource is designed to record patient referral information.

resource.name: Eswatini Specimen Profile
resource.description:
The Eswatini Specimen Profile is based on the FHIR Specimen resource. This profile sets minimum
expectation for Specimen resource to record information about substances associated with a patient or laboratory request being tested.
This profile specifies which core elements shall be present and how these elements are used.

resource.name: Eswatini Vital Signs Profile
resource.description:
This profile is based on the base FHIR Vital Signs Profile and defines additional constraints on the Observation resource to represent
vital signs observations specifically for Eswatini.
